# Public account exclusions (FROZEN)

Test / internal accounts must never appear mixed with live players on public surfaces.

## Hidden usernames

Canonical list: `cloudflare/monex-api/src/lib/public-account-exclusions.js` → `PUBLIC_HIDDEN_USERNAMES`.

Includes at least:
- `test` — staging / QA account
- `yesdraken_` — legacy wild-log hide

## Where they must be omitted

| Surface | Enforcement |
|---------|-------------|
| Campaign / Power leaderboards | Server `buildLeaderboard` skips hidden handles |
| Global X Wild Log (`GET /api/activity` without username) | Server `listActivities` + client filter |
| Future public arena / PvP boards | Reuse `isPublicHiddenUsername` — do not invent a second list |

## Still allowed

- Account can log in, play, save, and use personal `/api/activity/mine`
- Ops / admin tooling may still address the account by username

## One-line summary

**`test` (and other public-hidden handles) never show on rankings, wild log, or future public boards.**
